This paper focuses on improving the efficiency of data collection and curation pipelines for autonomous systems, specifically in the context of robot learning. The paper discusses three orthogonal fronts: imitation learning, domain adaptation, and transfer from simulation. These topics are all closely related to the field of robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.LG), as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and systems and control (cs.SY). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.RO, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, and cs.SY.
